<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1" />
  <title>Privacy Policy - OnlyFreds</title>
  
  <meta name="description" content="OnlyFreds Privacy Policy. How we handle your data, your cookies, and your soul.">
  <meta name="robots" content="noindex, follow">

  <link href="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/bootstrap@5.3.3/dist/css/bootstrap.min.css" rel="stylesheet">
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="/css/style.css"/>
  <link rel="icon" type="image/png" href="/img/OnlyFreds_logo.png"/>

  <style>
    .fade-in-section {
      opacity: 0;
      transform: translateY(40px);
      transition: opacity 1s ease-out, transform 1s ease-out;
      will-change: opacity, transform;
    }
    .fade-in-section.is-visible {
      opacity: 1;
      transform: none;
    }
    .section-spacer { padding: 5rem 0; }
    .legal-text { text-align: justify; }
  </style>
</head>
<body class="d-flex flex-column min-vh-100 bg-light">

  <%- include("partials/navbar") %>

  <section class="hero text-white text-center py-5 fade-in-section">
    <div class="container">
      <h1 class="display-4 fw-bold">Privacy Policy</h1>
      <p class="lead">Your secrets are safe with us (mostly)</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section-spacer fade-in-section">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="row justify-content-center">
        <div class="col-lg-10">
          <div class="card border-0 shadow-lg rounded-4 overflow-hidden">
            <div class="card-body p-5">
              
              <div class="alert alert-info border-0 rounded-3 mb-5 d-flex align-items-center">
                <span class="fs-2 me-3">ðŸ”’</span>
                <div>
                  <strong>TL;DR:</strong> We value your privacy. We do not sell your data to competitors, mainly because they are mostly dead or in prison.
                </div>
              </div>

              <h2 class="fw-bold text-primary mb-4">1. Information We Collect</h2>
              <p class="text-muted legal-text mb-4">
                We collect information you provide directly to us, such as your name, email address, and shipping details. Additionally, we may collect:
              </p>
              <ul class="text-muted mb-4">
                <li><strong>Device Information:</strong> We track which device you use to ensure it can handle high-resolution jumpscares.</li>
                <li><strong>Fear Metrics:</strong> (Optional) Biometric data on how fast you close the browser tab at 3 AM.</li>
                <li><strong>Pizza Preferences:</strong> Strictly for quality assurance purposes.</li>
              </ul>

              <h2 class="fw-bold text-primary mb-4">2. How We Use Your Data</h2>
              <p class="text-muted legal-text mb-4">
                We use your personal data to process orders and improve the OnlyFreds experience. We may also use your email to send you:
              </p>
              <ul class="text-muted mb-4">
                <li>Order confirmations.</li>
                <li>Password reset links.</li>
                <li>Cryptic lore drops that may or may not solve the story.</li>
              </ul>

              <h2 class="fw-bold text-primary mb-4">3. Cookies & Tracking</h2>
              <p class="text-muted legal-text mb-4">
                We use cookies to maintain your session and keep you logged in. These are standard digital cookies, not the delicious chocolate chip kind found in the kitchen. Please do not attempt to eat your monitor.
              </p>

              <h2 class="fw-bold text-primary mb-4">4. Data Security</h2>
              <p class="text-muted legal-text mb-4">
                We implement state-of-the-art security measures to protect your information. Our dedicated Security Officer, <strong>Fred</strong>, stands guard by the server room door. While his methods are unorthodox (mostly just staring menacingly), we have found them surprisingly effective against data breaches.
              </p>

              <h2 class="fw-bold text-primary mb-4">5. Third-Party Sharing</h2>
              <p class="text-muted legal-text mb-4">
                We do not share your personal information with third parties, except:
              </p>
              <ul class="text-muted mb-4">
                <li><strong>Fazbear Entertainment:</strong> For legal compliance and "cleanup" operations.</li>
                <li><strong>Service Providers:</strong> Brevo (for emails) and MongoDB (for database).</li>
              </ul>

              <h2 class="fw-bold text-primary mb-0">6. Changes to This Policy</h2>
              <p class="text-muted legal-text mb-0">
                We may update this privacy policy from time to time. If we make significant changes, we will notify you by playing a music box melody very slowly in your vicinity.
              </p>

            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <%- include("partials/footer") %>
  <script src="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/bootstrap@5.3.3/dist/js/bootstrap.bundle.min.js"></script>
  <script src="/script/navbar.js"></script>

  <script>
    document.addEventListener("DOMContentLoaded", function() {
      const observer = new IntersectionObserver((entries) => {
        entries.forEach(entry => {
          if (entry.isIntersecting) entry.target.classList.add('is-visible');
        });
      }, { threshold: 0.1 });
      document.querySelectorAll('.fade-in-section').forEach(section => observer.observe(section));
    });
  </script>
</body>
</html>